        "client_msg_id": "cbad7a0c-bace-4e82-b0ab-52a270a04f12",
        "text": "To anyone here who has done what we do here exclusively for a period of time (and hence has a gap in CV). What approach did you take with explaining the gap? I am making tentative steps towards looking for employment again, simply because I want to be able to get a mortgage, but I am reluctant to explicitly put things like \"professional gambler\" on the CV for obvious reasons. Currently I have a single sentence description explaining the \"gap\" inside an generic overview section. I am curious to know what others have done in the past, or what those of you who currently recruit would see as red flags? As someone who used to select interview candidates from CV batches I would almost always put anything with a gap to the bottom of the pile (not saying that was the right thing to do, just acknowledging the reality of the situation). Any suggestions?",
